<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="478" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1304,1545]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,259,1448,1472]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Remarks:</emphasis>
Although no specific locality in the Kalahari was indicated by Simon for this species, all other species mentioned in this paper and that of Purcell (1908) from the Kalahari were from localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[944,1044,1485,1508]" name="Botswana" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Botswana</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1058,1117,1484,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1461,1486]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,413,1440]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,413,1450]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Map of southern Africa, indicating localities sampled during the Schultze expedition in Botswana (BOT), Namibia (NAM) and the Republic of South Africa (RSA). Locality numbers in the key correspond to co-ordinates in Table 1 and dubious localities are indicated by a?. Localities are listed in alphabetical order by country. One locality, Kugukup in Botswana, could not be traced." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3066774/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), so it is likely that this species was also collected there.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
